                <div class = 'weight-info'>
                	<p>
                    	I admit it! I'm not the biggest user of cardiovascular routines. I'm lazy and like to sit on my ass and occasionally
                        lift heavy ass weights. But there has been times where I have tried different fitness routines, and if you're looking
                        to start and need some ideas you'll get my experience right here right now.
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    	Couch to 5k is a brillant routine to follow for beginners, I mean I came from only lifting weights to end
                        up being able to jog for a continious 30 mins, something before hand I thought I'd never ever be able to do.
                        The plan is spanned over 9 weeks, with each week progressivly getting more challenging.
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    	At the first couple of weeks you'll think its piss easy breasing through with not a problem, but then things
                        start to change and you'll be stirring at the clock like your life depended on it! I remember in particular the jump
                        from week 4 to 5 being the stuff of nightmares, I dreaded that friday so much!
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    	But I surpised myself with what I could do and learned a lesson about how far you can go by not giving up!
                        In truth I never finished the routine to 100% completion I was able to jog 30 mins but wasnt quite fast enough
                        to hit 3 miles but I was making progress and then I landed a full time job so I had to stop (excuses!) and
                        concentrate on my main love, Weights(Pizza).
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    	It is a great beginner routine, if it helped me and got me to the end it will work for anyone thats puts
                        the time and effort into it! I would say if you are over weight by alot, this routine might be too sore on the
                        joints and you would be better of trying something with less impact such as swimming or a bike for example.
                    </p>
                    
                    <p>
                    	For more information <a href = 'http://www.coolrunning.com/engine/2/2_3/181.shtml'>Link</a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
